node.text:
IT'S THE NPS-AVERSARY!
From the early days of "hey, maybe we should keep this place wild", through pivotal moments of the very fabric of modern American history, the NPS continues to protect and preserve the places that make us who we are. 
Today marks 103 years of National Parks Service – we think a toast is in order! Video by @maxeyfish #radparks #findyourpark

node.title: The (unofficial) History of the National Parks

Back by popular demand, the @parksproject x @igloocoolers ECO-COOL™️ playmate is ready for your next campout, lake day, or afternoon picnic. node.text:
We love to see siblings getting along! Three Brothers, one of the many iconic rock formations in @Yosemitenps, offers spectacular views of the valley below. The hike to the top is roughly 7 miles, averaging 4.5 hours up and 3.5 hours down, so be sure to plan for a full day of hiking, and don't forget to pack a lunch 🥪  #leaveitbetter #radparks #findyourpark

Photo by @v_outdoors
📍Photo taken on Northern Paiute, Western Mono/Monache, Central Sierra Miwok, and Southern Sierra Miwok native lands.

Stargazing in @Deathvalleynps is outta this world 🚀 Due to the isolated location and minimal light pollution, Death Valley offers spectacular views of the Milky Way Galaxy, along with a never ending blanket of stars. Have you seen this park after dark?

node.text:
Did you know Mount Rainier was not this peak's original name? Local tribes referred to the mountain  as Tacoma or Tahoma, meaning “the source of nourishment from the many streams coming from the slopes.” A fitting name as there are 5 major rivers that originate from the glaciated peak and hundreds of waterfalls in the park as a result!

node.text:
One of the most iconic landmarks in the country, this granite giant draws avid hikers from all over the world with its 16-mile roundtrip hike. Curious about hiking Half Dome? Make sure you are properly prepared:

🌲 Have the proper permit.
⛰️ Make sure you are physically fit - this is a strenuous 10-12 hour trek with a 4,800 feet elevation gain.
🌊 Pack plenty of water; much of the trail is exposed to the elements.
👣 Wear proper hiking attire.
🏞️ Always practice Leave No Trace principles.
